This is a placeholder file. To create an actual Excel example, create a file with the following structure:

Column A: Camera Name (optional - will create camera automatically)
Column B: IP Address (optional - used for both branch and camera)  
Column C: Branch Name (required)
Column D: Phone Number (optional)

Example data:
| A         | B             | C     | D           |
|-----------|---------------|-------|-------------|
| كاميرا 1  | 192.168.1.1   | فرع 1 | 01234567890 |
| كاميرا 2  | 192.168.1.2   | فرع 2 | 01123456789 |
| كاميرا 3  | 192.168.1.3   | فرع 3 | 01098765432 |
|           | 192.168.1.4   | فرع 4 | 01555555555 |

Features:
- Only Column C (Branch Name) is required
- If Column A has camera name, a camera will be created automatically for that branch
- If branch already exists, camera will be added/updated
- Duplicate branch names can be skipped with the checkbox option
- IP address from Column B will be used for both branch and camera

Camera Creation Logic:
- New branch + camera name = Creates both branch and camera
- Existing branch + camera name = Adds/updates camera in existing branch
- Existing branch + existing camera name = Updates camera IP if provided
- No camera name = Only creates/updates branch
